      <hedline>
        <hl1>Microsoft Breakup: A Serious Mistake</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Blair Schofield letter warns that breaking up Microsoft would cripple major segment of US economy (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Microsoft Breakup Is Ordered for Antitrust Violations'' (front page, June 8):</p>
        <p>Judge Thomas Penfield Jackson has ordered Microsoft to be split into two separate companies. Unless Microsoft wins on appeal, this ruling will cripple a major segment of the American economy, and possibly damage many retirement funds.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Microsoft Breakup Is Ordered for Antitrust Violations'' (front page, June 8):</p>
        <p>Judge Thomas Penfield Jackson has ordered Microsoft to be split into two separate companies. Unless Microsoft wins on appeal, this ruling will cripple a major segment of the American economy, and possibly damage many retirement funds.</p>
        <p>One should take a moment to seek out the motivation behind the attacks, both from industry and government, on one of America's greatest and most successful companies.</p>
        <p>BLAIR SCHOFIELD  New Britain, Conn., June 8, 2000</p>
      </block>
